verbs.description: prehend (third-person singular simple present prehends, present participle prehending, simple past and past participle prehended)

entries.meaning: (philosophy) To perceive in the manner of Alfred North Whitehead's concept of prehension.
(obsolete) To lay hold of; to seize.
